  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Providing nutrient rich meals, like those provided by Rise Against Hunger, in food insecure communities is Convoy of Hope&#x2019;s (COH) initial step in its strategy to address hunger and undernutrition.COH&#x2019;s holistic approach includes interventions that are nutrition-specific, addressing immediate needs, nutrition-sensitive, supporting long-term food security initiatives such as agricultural training and access to clean water, and that build an enabling environment for sustainable development such as micro-enterprise initiatives. Rise Against Hunger meals will serve 6,500 beneficiaries in Honduras in 60 feeding centers such as public and private schools in areas where food insecurity is greatest as determined by annual needs assessments.</narrative>
  </description>
